<br>
&quot;Yes, we are moving toward making Wizards the master of arcane transportation. This seems like the right direction to take the class.&quot; <br>
<br>
Alan<br>
<br>
<br>
Here we go. <br>
<br>
Call of Heroes – Give it to us. Unique to Mages? Only if Verant wants it to be. There are many spells that are shared among different classes. THIS should be one of them! Should also make Wizards more “Group Friendly”<br>
<br>
Enduring Breath – We should have had this long ago as a self only buff.<br>
<br>
Personal Gates – Need to be redone. Wizards should have a personal gate to EVERY zone in the game. In addition, it should put them down in the zone “Safe Spot” not at a spire or pyramid unless that happens to be the SS.<br>
<br>
Group Portals – Add a few new ones to compensate for the lack of other traveling magics. Everfrost, Field of Bone and Trakannon’s Teeth (near old Sebilis, I can’t believe a place THAT steeped in magic had or has no portal site)<br>
<br>
Translocate Line – PLEASE stop playing this up as a benefit for Wizards! Nice spells, but they earn no exp, get no other groups, cost mana and take time (even more now with the confirmation box) Remove the need to be grouped to use ie. SoW and Rez.<br>
<br>
Relocation Line – Remove the need for being in a dungeon to cast.<br>
<br>
Abscond / Evacuate – Casting time on these should be cut in half.<br>
<br>
Gate – Gate is our only reasonable personal escape. Casting time should be on par with Enchanter AE stuns, Necro / SK Feign Death. I’m thinking 2.0 seconds at MOST.<br>
<br>
Fade Line – Tricky programming here. I admit this is a tough one. I’d like to see this put the caster at the bottom of the Hate list ( ala EVADE for rogues). This way it is not an escape while soloing but can help in group situations where the caster has aggroed the mob. Rename the spells so this modified line is unique to Wizards ( I believe the only other classes that get these spells have Feign death) Lower the cast time to 2.0 at MOST.<br>
<br>
Evacuate Line – Remove the possibility of leaving someone behind or, and I REALLY hate saying this, make the Druid version less reliable. Groups should have to trade off escaping reliably for taking a different class with other specialties. Lower the casting time. THESE should go off FAST. I’d say double the casting time of Gate after IT has been modified.<br>
<br>
General – ALL Transportation spells should have there levels lowered so they are available before ANY other class. Mana costs should be lowered as these spells are utility only.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
<br>
Wish List<br>
<br>
New Spell: Denizen – This would work in a similar way to Monster Summoning Line only, it would give the wizard the ILLUSION of a zone NPC and an Indifferent faction in that zone. Most of the programming exists for this, just need to put it together. Illusions are not unique to Enchanters, Bards and Rogues get item illusions to aid them and they can have Sneak and Hide.<br>
<br>
New Spell Line: Vanish / Improved Vanish – A combination Invisibility and Invisibility to Undead. Again, this already exists. Improved Vanish would also add Plainsight and Levitate.<br>
<br>
Quests – Quests for items to aid in traveling. I’d like to see a new set of Wizard only Boots, that are an improvement over Journeyman’s Boots. Call them “Traveler’s Boots”. Give them AC, SoW speed (Spirit of Cheetah and Bard Songs are faster than SoW) and Levitate.<br>
<br>
Quests – Quests based on Traveling. These should not require groups, but planning , stealth, travel, lots of NO RENT items and MAYBE a little combat. I’d love to see a quest that took 12 hours full of NO RENT items, if the prize was worth it.<br>
<br>
Lock Down the Planes – There should be NO way to get to the Plane without a Wizard PERIOD. It took me 6 months to get back into Fear after you removed the need for Alter Plane Fear spell.<br>
<br>
<br>
I’m confident that nothing listed would significantly alter game balance. Moreover they make sense, given Verant’s position on the “direction to take the class”<br>
<br>
I hope to see a response posted from Verant, at least we would have an Idea where you are taking the Wizard Class. I know there are many out there like me, who would like to know if we should stop wasting out time.<br>
<br>
<br>
Knemays, 55th Level Wizard of Trinity Alliance, Prexus Server<br>
